    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4457/1–2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 14, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 199—Bulgarian Series.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch (No. 192) of the 21st
                    ultimo, I have the honor to transmit herewith a copy<note n="a" xml:id="d101fna"
                        >Not printed.</note> (in French) of the commercial and customs arrangement
                    which was concluded between the Ottoman Empire and the principality of Bulgaria
                    on December 30, 1906 (old style), which has just been sent me by the ministry of
                    foreign affairs at Sofia. This arrangement went into effect on January 1/14. In
                    general it is of the most-favored-nation character (Arts. II and III), with such
                    modifications as are necessitated by circumstances and the existence of a long
                    and ill-defined frontier. According to Article VI, no transit dues are to be
                    charged on Bulgarian goods passing through the Ottoman Empire.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Jackson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
